text:
This incident should also bring the government’s attention to a wider problem of deforestation along the way up to Genting starting from past Gombak toll.

For the past 5-10 years more and more trees along the hill got cleared otw driving up to Genting, some were for agricultural and homestay while others for property development.  

The serious landslides last year Dec 2021 along the way up to Genting should have served a warning sign that it’s starting to see overdevelopment esp those approved properties projects.  

Hopefully under your administration the relevant ministries would set a proper planning to protect the forest and limit the over development along Genting.  Let’s hope not to see the repeating mistakes of Cameron Highlands in Genting
